description: Mia is asleep and fantasizing that she is the new Speedy. Furthermore, she is fantasizing of making out with Ollie. Ollie wakes her up and tells her that she is late for school. As Mia jumps into the shower, Ollie finds a crossbow hidden behind her bed. Mia confesses that she wants to become Ollie's new sidekick.
name: Ultimate Speedy

deck: The first appearance of Kevin Smith's bizarre Onomatopoeia.
description:
The story opens at JSA headquarters, where Stargirl tells Black Canary that Green Arrow has shown up to take her out to dinner. Upon hearing that Courtney left him alone downstairs with Hawkman, Dinah races downstairs before the two philosophically opposed heroes kill one another. But rather than a fight, she finds that they are laughing and carrying on as if they were best friends. Ollie and Dinah go out to dinner, and she discloses her recent dating history, including Ra's Al Ghul and her then-JSA teammate Doctor Midnite, which provokes some jealousy in Oliver. Canary is initially put-off by this, but Arrow then confesses that when he was dead, she was one of his primary motivations for struggling to live again. Before the conversation can go any further, their night is interrupted by the Riddler and his henchmen, intent on robbing the restaurant-goers. The heroes make quick work of them, and leave to share more intimate moments. In the afterglow, Oliver is confronted by Hawkman, who is being protective of his teammate; this fight occurs in the next issue.

This issue also leads in to "The Sounds of Violence," Smith's last story arc on his initial run on the book. In Philadelphia, a young heroine named Virago is stalked and murdered by the enigmatic Onomatopoeia, a serial killer who targets non-powered costumed heroes.
name: Feast and Fowl

description: Lacuna part 1
name: Lacuna: Part One: Captain Coconut

description: The team confronts a fame-hungry mutant with the power to freeze time. How can they chase her away when she can slip between the seconds?
name: Lacuna: Part Two: Larry King Has the Flu

description: 'Nuff Said' silent issue. In this issue, Doop pops a zit on his forehead which opens up a portal inside of him that sucks the X-Force team inside... and he somehow goes inside of himself to get them out of wildly strange situations and back to reality before the minute they were sucked inside of him within is over.
name: Tick Tock

description: In this issue, U-Go-Girl opens up to Orphan about her past as their relationship blossoms.
name: Edie and Guy Finally Do It

description: Part 1 of X-Force's final mission with the X-Force moniker as Dead Girl joins the team.
name: One of Us

description: This is no nostalgia trip, True Believers! Just as the original series dealt with the important matters of the day, the new HOWARD tackles the big issues, starting with that scourge of the modern world: Boy Bands! "Making the Band" is classic satire in the Gerber/Howard tradition, with all the added creative freedom that the MAX line allows! Trapped on a world he never made, Howard himself will be lucky to survive his encounter with the corporate music world... unchanged! What do we mean by that? Just check out the cover to the debut issue by painter Glenn Fabry!

As a duck, Howard never fit in on our world, but now he's becoming something even stranger! See what happens when your girlfriend's ex comes back into her life! The mind-bending transformations and social satire continue here!
name: It Came From The Shower!

description:
There exists an ancient and powerful amulet called the Amulet of Pazuzu that turns its wearer into a giant-breasted killing machine and turns itself into a blade called the Doucheblade... three guesses as to of what that's a spoof.

Wielders of the Doucheblade include Vicki of Humbabu, Suzi Pazuzu, Hatshesut of Egypt, Hippolyta, Joan of Arc, Jane Austen, Queen Victoria, Eleanor Roosevelt, and... Howard the Duck!?

Beverly Switzler and Howard the Duck have faced some strange challenges in their time, but nothing as frightening, as disorienting, as anxious-making as... The Boarding House of Mystery! Who is the gonzo journalist who speaks with the voice of God? What is the gas-masked performance artist known as Anthrax Mystery Theatre?

While Howard and Beverly try to deal with the insane journalist Splatter Gomorrah, the heaven-spawned super-creature called Deuteronomy merges with America's favorite talk-show host! Also starring the man called Hellboozer! This issue brings new meaning to the term "mature readers comics"!

Veteran AVENGERS scribe Steve Englehart returns for an all-new cosmic saga! The flaring of a star in the night sky signals the dawning of the age of the Celestial Messiah, the offspring of the former Avenger known as Mantis. But this is an age that the mad titan Thanos will do anything to prevent, even if he must kill the Celestial Madonna time after time after time! Once again the fate of the universe rests in the hands of Thor, Vision, Scarlet Witch and Earth's Mightiest Heroes! If you're a fan of sprawling sagas, then this one's for you! THE WRITER SPEAKS: "The series, amazingly enough, is Mantis vs. Thanos, which is to say, we watch each side of the conflict as it builds toward its climax," explained Englehart. "It's not all about Mantis with an occasional foray by the villain; each half of this equation has a story to be told. Of course, Mantis and Thanos aren`t alone in this thing. She`s got a small group of Avengers on her side: Thor, Vision, Wanda, and Silverclaw. They`re joined by Haywire of the Squadron Supreme, who's hoping to get his dead girlfriend back. And yes, Mantis and Vision get it on."
name: I Die Unknown

description: Whole once more, Mantis -- and her Avengers allies -- must take to the stars to prevent Thanos from locating and eliminating the long-hidden Celestial Messiah!
name: Madonna Reborn

description:
Overview

DC's newest super-team debuts in its own ongoing series! When the Power Company has to confront the mysterious machinations of Doctor Cyber, the team may find itself out of business before they've had a chance to set up shop.
name: Executive Search

description: The adventures of the DC Universe's newest super-team sensation continue! The Power Company finds out that its first challenge, the superpowered mercenaries called Strike Force, is only the precursor to a larger, more deadly challenge: the monstrous Dragoneer! And what is the connection to Wonder Woman's old enemy, Dr. Cyber? Will the Power Company be forced to close its doors when business has barely begun?
name: Here There Be Dragons

description: Those of you with stock in the newest name in super-hero services may want to reconsider, because the team is about to crash hard! The Dragoneer is using the Godstone to bring forth an undreamed-of evil, and it's becoming more and more obvious that nothing will stop him, not even the Power Company. Meanwhile the threat of Dr. Cyber and her hired thugs, the Strike Force, still looms large. Wounded and beaten, the Company may be out of business before its first mission is even completed.
name: Something Wicked This Way Comes...

description: John Francis Moore begins a startling 3-issue story. For months, there have been two Catwomans running around, but the truth behind the matter lies in a most unexpected place, as Catwoman discovers someone very close has turned on her! And if she didn't have enough problems already, what the heck is she doing breaking into Arkham Asylum?!
name: The End  -- of the Illusion!

description: Sometimes ignorance is better than the truth, and after what Selina Kyle learned about the second Catwoman last issue, she's wishing she never got out of bed! But that's small potatoes compared to facing off with the one villain who's been able to get under her skin: the Scarecrow. If Selina doesn't take the straw man down, she's finished. But with her psyche so fractured, can she ever hope to survive?
name: The End -- of the Charade!

description:
Final Issue! Selina may have beaten back the source of the inner demons that have plagued her, but that doesn't mean she's cured. Time is running out, and she's got to get out of Gotham!

Final issue. It's the end of Catwoman as readers knew her, as the series goes out with a bang. Selina may have beaten back the source of the inner demons that have plagued her, but that doesn't mean she's cured. Time is running out, and she's got to get out of Gotham - quickly. Meanwhile, Deathstroke is in town, and he's got more than sight-seeing planned. Note: Be sure to check out the 4-part backup serial starting next month in Detective Comics #759, as legendary DC character Slam Bradley begins his search for Catwoman.
name: The End of Catwoman!

description: Lucifer Morningstar returns to Hell in this fifth collection of the acclaimed LUCIFER series, reprinting issues #29-35. Still weak, with most of his power locked in the feathers stolen by Susano-O-No-Mikoto, Lucifer must now face the challenge of single combat to the death with his brother, the angel of the Host Amenadiel. But as Mazikeen hunts for Susano and Lucifer plans his strategy, angels and devils alike are plotting for his defeat even before the challenge has begun!
name: Vol. 5

description: Sometimes risqué, but never routine…and always over the top. Welcome to the world of Earl Dorian Red Gloria, a glamorous, hedonistic art collector who secretly lives a double life as the thief known as Eroica. FROM EROICA WITH LOVE traces the course of the Earl as he prances flamboyantly all over Europe in search of new thrills. Adding to the heady mix of intrigue, adventure and humor, is a cast of unforgettable characters, including the ultraconservative but dashing NATO intelligence officer who finds himself time and time again entangled in the Earl's affairs and arms. In this second volume, the relationship between the Earl and the NATO officer reaches a whole new level. This volume also includes a bonus story by the author in which a new officer discovers much more than he bargained for on a ship that's all play and no work.

On this third volume of FROM EROICA WITH LOVE Eroica and the German officer, Eberbach, both with different agendas, yet after the same thing, steal into Iran during the height of the Islamic Revolution. Eberbach is ordered to hire Gloria much to his distaste. And as always, young men are seduced, a war erupts, friends are betrayed, and sexual preferences are explored.

Major Eberbach has been ordered to hire international playboy thief Eroica to steal military secrets for NATO in Rome! But Eroica's ego demands a bigger prize than mere documents! A crisis erupts as the KGB, the Italian police, the Mafia, and the Roman Catholic Church are ensnared in Eroica's scheme!

The fan-favorite spy saga continues! A sunken World War II relic holds the secrets Eroica, the Major, and a KGB agent desperately want. For Eroica and the gang, the prize will be riches beyond their wildest dreams. It's a mission of utmost importance (as usual) for the Major, but an old and vengeful nemesis, Mischa the Bear Cub, wants the secrets to destroy the Major — and the West!

When the British Crown goes on exhibit in Germany, the Major knows Eroica is bound to follow. NATO, the CIA and even the KGB conspire to lure the world's most elegant art thief away from the world's most irresistible jewels. Will Eroica take the bait?

The world's most flamboyant art thief and his hard-nosed NATO nemesis continue their globe-spanning contest of wills! First the Major had to protect the British crown. Now, with the entire world watching him–and what could be worse for a secret agent?–he must protect the Queen of England herself. But in the end, it's Eroica who looks to be wearing the crown. As for the Major, his day is about to get worse–much worse!

The Major is delivering a secret document to NATO when his flight is hijacked. The plane also carries a famous painting that Eroica desires. Not even a hijacking can deter the world's most flamboyant art thief, but there's more to these terrorists than meets the eye. And Klaus may have to face his worst nightmare: joining forces (again!) with Eroica to stop the terrorists!

"Seven Days in September" continues as the Major and his K.G.B. nemesis square off in Spain over the crucial Lubyanka Report. The report lands in the hands of Eroica, who hopes to trade it to the Major for "The Man in Purple," the painting he covets. To capture the Earl, Klaus finds himself a reluctant ally to a Kuwaiti oil magnate whom Eroica swindled once before.

"Seven Days in September" concludes, as Eroica faces a climactic showdown against Saleem — the vengeful oil magnate — on the grounds of an Egyptian ruin. Meanwhile, the Major battles the KGB with the fate of the coveted Lubyanka report in the balance. In a second story, Eroica finds himself in the middle of a surprise party for his adversary, Iron Klaus!

When Eroica discovers the owner of a large supermarket chain has purchased a Swiss Abbey and plans to demolish it, he concocts an elaborate hoax to save it. Of course his motives are less than holy; he's learned the abbey is filled with priceless medieval art. And as their always-intertwined fates would have it, Eroica's rival "Iron Klaus" ends up at the same abbey in pursuit of some hidden microfilm.

FROM EROICA WITH LOVE is the masterwork manga of Aoike Yasuko, serialized in Akita Shoten's Princess magazine since 1976! Set in Continental Europe, it depicts the adventures of British aristocrat Dorian Red Gloria and his alter ego Eroica, Europe's most wanted international art thief. His nemesis — Major Klaus Heinz von dem Eberbach, a German NATO intelligence officer — has tried for years to catch the man who claims each crime scene with a card signed "From Eroica with Love." Things are just getting started when a trio of telepathically linked teenagers becomes aware of Dorian's identity and plans to capture him. But their plot goes awry as the master thief branches out — no longer content with stealing great art, he's moving on. Now the trio must foil his attempts to kidnap their leader, Caesar, as they try to save the great art treasures of Europe!

Do vampires really walk the Earth? They do, but so do a band of super-powered vampire hunters. Led by a reluctant teenaged heroine who, transformed by the bite of the undead into the Scarlett Redeemer, is driven to find the brutal murderers of her parents. She is Bly Pharis, last hope of an immortal order of vampire slayers. Her prey is Sunset Sam and his fearsome group of vampire bikers who represent only the vanguard of a savage, secret culture of the undead. SCARLETT is the story of an ages-old struggle, set in the present day, outside the DC Universe; a struggle where the undead threaten humanity, and only the dedication of a small group of specially trained, uniquely-bred warriors stands before the triumph of the undead and mankind's obliteration.
name: Blood of Innocence

description: Bly and Paul are prisoners of Sunset Sam and his gang of vampire bikers, the Road Disciples. But that could be a blessing in disguise for Bly, who's being hunted by the police for the murder of her parents.
name: Blood Of Innocence Chapter 3

description: Bly Pharis is dead, a stake driven through her heart. Hope for the birth of the Scarlett Redeemer, immortal slayer of vampires, may have died with her. In the Arizona desert, a supernatural maelstrom builds as warring factions of human and undead strike to either kindle that hope...or see it crushed forever. The newest of the factions is the hi-tech soldiers of S.A.V.E. (Society for Advancement of Vampire Ecology).
name: Blood Of Innocence Chapter 4

description: Bly Pharis rises from death to assume her destiny as the Scarlett Redeemer and finds herself in the midst of a swirling battle involving two warring factions of vampires, their near-immortal foes, the Nomads, the mysterious vampire stalker, Montero, and the unraveling of the very fabric of reality.
name: Blood of Innocence Chapter 4

description: The Scarlett Redeemer, scourge of vampires and heir to the future of the Nomad race, has been born. Now learn the history of the mysterious Nomads and the ancient origin of their eternal battle against vampires.
name: Blood of the Ancients-The First Dreamwalk

description: An amnesiac Bly Pharis, still reeling from her recent death/rebirth experience as the Scarlett Redeemer, lies helpless in the hospital. Enter vampire queen Harmony Hamashita and her pet werewolves, ready to cut short Scarlett's threat to her unholy empire.
name: Blood of the Damned: Chapter One

description: Scarlett's already on the run from the police, the Nomads and the Vampiric Clave. Now enter the Blood Wing - Shadowclaw, Homunculus and Sunblight - a superpolished strike force out to capture Bly at any cost.
name: Blood of the Damned: Chapter 2

description: Captured by the Blood Wing, Scarlett is trapped in a city of vampires...and all are out for her blood!
name: Blood of the Damned: Chapter 3

description: Caught between warring vampire factions, Scarlett must battle her way out of a city of the undead.
name: Blood of the Damned Chapter 4

description:
With half the Legion gone, the 30th century's remaining heroes realize they can't safeguard the galaxy alone, so (you knew this was coming)...it's time once again for the Legionnaire Try-Outs! An open audition means that Legion HQ is overrun with prospective applicants, many of them possessing more "personality" than actual ability. But by issue's end, several new Legionnaires are inducted to carry on the team's heroic tradition!

The Legion of Super-Heroes hold tryouts for new members.
name: New Blood

description: The new Legionnaires become the object of a revenge plot by several of last issue's rejected Legionnaire applicants! Plus, it's Lori's birthday...and she can cry if she wants to!
name: Rookies To The Rescue!

description:
The Legionnaires sizzle when a mission to Vyrga (Gates' home planet) uncovers a horrifying mutant beast that is terrorizing the inhabitants. Meanwhile, M'onel's search for the Emerald Empress heats up.

Mantis Morlo is attacking the planet Vryga and its people demand that Legionnaire Gates return to assist them. The only problem is that Gates is lost in the timestream with the other Legionnaires, so what's the team to do? Give the Vrygan people what they want.
name: Vendetta on Vyrga!

description: Metropolis in the 30th century provides the backdrop for this multi-faceted story, as M'onel's life hangs by a thread. A mysterious figure pursues an ancient quest for power; Dreamer reveals more about her startling visions; and Chameleon finds a soulmate. Plus, Kinetix under attack! Or is she?
name: Grip of Terror

description: One of the 20th century Legionnaires is in a coma, and Brainiac 5 rises to the occasion, coming up with a risky method of getting everyone back to the future. But due to unexpected treachery from within the team, the rescue attempt fails and all of the Legionnaires are trapped in the timestream!
name: Lost in Time

description: Mordru has returned and he wants the Emerald Eye!
name: Dawn of the Dark Lord

description: The Legionnaires prepare for their epic battle with the sinister sorcerer Mordru by combing the galaxy for more heroes to join in the fight! But the battle may be over before it begins when Element Lad is gravely injured and Andromeda refuses to re-join.
name: Let the Call Go Forth

description: As part of his plan to rule the universe, the evil wizard Mordru has formed an alliance with the mystically powerful Emerald Eye. Unfortunately, this alliance has taken the form of a wedding between Shrinking Violet and the sinister sorcerer himself!
name: The Bride of Mordru

description: The Legionnaires deal with the aftermath of the battle with Mordru, including the very real possibility that they may not be able to permanently imprison the sorcerer!
name: ... The Survivors!

description: Shrinking Violet has had a tough time of it lately—unfortunately, there's still more trouble ahead when a mysterious transformation overcomes her.
name: LeViathan!

description: "Dark Circle Rising" Part 3! Continued from LEGION OF SUPER-HEROES (1989) #106! The Dark Circle's actions continue to tear the United Planets apart, and it's affected the Legion's ranks as well. Continued in LEGION OF SUPER-HEROES (1989) #107!
name: Winds of War?

description:
"Dark Ciricle Rising" Part 5! Continued from LEGION OF SUPER-HEROES (1989) #107! To confuse the United Planets concerning its true intentions, the Dark Circle has declared war on Durla, Chameleon's homeworld. Continued in LEGION OF SUPER-HEROES (1989) #108!

The strange space anomaly has been exploited by the Dark Circle, causing it to seizure and time itself to freeze. The Legionnaires who have previously time travelled are free to move about in frozen time and must find a way to both restore the movement of time and find a way to subdue the war overhead.
name: Dark Circle Rising, Part 5: Time Out!

description: The rift between the United Planets and the Affiliated Planets continues to grow, as even more worlds secede from the U.P. And one Legionnaire is torn by the discovery of the Dark Circle leader's identity!
name: Days of Reckoning!

description:
A solo espionage adventure starring Invisible Kid! Lyle goes off on his own in search of his long-lost friend Jacques Foccart. His search leads him to a club owned by another former spy from his past: Mara Grace, also known as Charma!

Invisible Kid has been captured by the irresistible Charma as revenge for their spy days. The two recount their individual origins before Invisible Kid's restraints are suspiciously freed for him. Meanwhile, Shrinking Violet and Chuck Taine go out on a date around Metropolis.
name: Missing Persons

description:
A mysterious cave-in at a tourist park may turn to tragedy for a child unless Legionnaires Element Lad, Ferro, and Star Boy can find him.

A thief named Kono steals a precious resource in a cave that causes it to collapse, trapping a young boy inside. Ferro, Element Lad, and Star Boy are resolved to free the youth but Star Boy's continuously malfunctioning powers may begin doing more harm than good on their delicate search and rescue.
name: Here be Heroes!

description:
While assisting the Space and Time Museum with documenting his recent experiences in the 20th century, Cosmic Boy is attacked by Xotar the Conqueror!

Xotar the Conquerer materializes in the robotics section of the Time Institute of the 30th century, quickly dispatching the antique machines to do his bidding. Cosmic Boy intercepts them and calls in for back-up. Meanwhile, Monstress and Kid Quantum II are trying to enjoy a nice day of shopping when Monstress' skin color begins to rapidly change without warning. A colorful Monstress joins her fellow Legionnaires in taking down Xotar's forces.
name: When Robots Attack

description:
Lori Morning is tired of the Legionnaires treating her like a little kid. She has super-powers, and they still won't make her a member. But when a crisis breaks out on Lunabase, she finds another opportunity knocking!

Lori Morning continues to use her H-Dial to secretly assist the Legionnaires, this time against Khund forces attacking Earth's moon. Her identity is spilled when she is unable to leave a team-up with the Legionnaires and Workforce before her dialed power wears off. While the Legionnaires are aghast at Lori's desire to be a hero, Leland McCauley admits he has no such reservations and even goes so far as to invite Lori to join his Workforce despite the fact she's a minor. Mad with the Legion and enticed with finally getting the chance to play hero, Lori knee-jerk accepts Leland's offer and unsurely leaves the Legionnaires behind.
name: Secrets And Lies

description:
After serving time for his crimes, Cuspin seeks revenge on Cosmic Boy and hires the assassin called Domain, whose power to pull his victims into other dimensions has deadly results!

Cosmic Boy's former Magnoball manager, Alux Cuspin, hires the assassin Domain to take out his wayward protege. Domain transports Cosmic Boy, his brother Pol, and two bystanders from their Magnoball game into a dangerous dimension of traps intended to kill the occupants.
name: Enter: Domain

description: Dragonmage has inadvertently unleashed the Elementals of Disaster. With Earth as their target, only the Legion stands in their way, but, unbeknownst to our heroes, there's another player involved in this battle!
name: The Elements of Disaster

description: The Legionnaires have fallen prey to the Elements, and Star Boy must stand against them on his own!
name: The Final Gathering

description:
Star Boy's home planet Xanthu is attacked by the Khunds, and the Legionnaire must join with his old teammates—the Uncanny Amazers—to save their world!

Star Boy and Monstress return to their homeworld of Xanthu after a communications blackout. While the rest of the galaxy has written it off as standard Xanthu failure from being a border world, the Legionnaires quickly discover that Xanthu is in fact in the middle of an invasion. Teaming with the Uncanny Amazers, specifically Kid Quantum II, the Legionnaires help protect the innocent and get to the bottom of the invasive forces just as a group of Khunds swoop in to take the glory of victory. Suspicious of the Khunds, Star Boy and Monstress resolve to investigate and Star Boy inadvertently invites Kid Quantum to the Legion - which she surprisingly accepts after previously condemning the team.
name: Heroes

description:
Star Boy and the group on Xanthu are in deep, deep trouble when they're ambushed by two evil alien races while trying to save the planet from coming under the control of a third!

Karate Kid flees Leland McCauley's Workforce after sabotaging his latest experiment.
name: A Storm In Heaven

description: The rescue team returns from the space anomaly - with many of the members strangely changed - and with a new mystery.
name: From Out of the Void

description: "Adventures in Action" Part 2! Continued from LEGIONNAIRES #61! The Time Trapper confronts the Legionnaires with versions of themselves from alternate timelines!
name: Reality Check

description: "Dark Circle Rising" Part 2! Continued from LEGIONNAIRES #62! The twin presidents of Winath have been assassinated, and the murderer is...Chameleon?! Continued in LEGIONNAIRES #63!
name: Dark Circle Rising!, Part 2: High Crimes

description: "Dark Circle Rising" Part 4! Continued from LEGIONNAIRES #63! The ranks of the Legion have been weakened, making the time ripe for an attack by a Durlan with the powers of all the Legionnaires! Continued in LEGIONNAIRES #64!
name: Brainspotting: Dark Circle Rising, Part 4

description: "Dark Circle Rising" Part 6! Continued from LEGIONNAIRES #64! The disastrous aftermath of the Durlan war! But even if the Legion should emerge victorious, the tables may yet be turned when we find out who's been in charge of the Dark Circle all along!
name: Dark Circle Rising!, Part 6: The End

description: A special issue focusing on Violet! It's Vi's worst nightmare come true, as the Emerald Eye returns to take control of the Legionnaire once and for all!
name: Wish Fulfillment

description:
When Dr. Savant--mad leader of a magic-hating 30th century suicide cult on the planet Fawcettworld--blows up the Rock of Eternity, the heroine from a future even more distant than the Legion's is stranded in the 30th century!

Hurled through time thanks to an explosion of the Rock of Eternity, the super-heroine Thunder emerges in the 30th century with the debris of the Rock. Learning she has journeyed from the 20th century she was visiting back into the future by several Legionnaires, Thunder incorrectly assumes she's near her home time of the 85th century. She flies to her homeworld of Binderaan only to find it hasn't even been colonized yet, finally accepting her situation. When Fawcett World, also tied like Thunder to the Shazam mythos, is under attack, Thunder assists the Legionnaires in defending the planet. At the end of the adventure, she is invited to stay with the Legion and accepts membership into the team assigned to the Legion Outpost.
name: Where There's Lightning

description:
An intangible alien takes control of M'Onel and Thunder to rid his planet of all offworlders and pits the strongest Legionnaires against their teammates.

M'Onel and Thunder are possessed by xenophobic spirits from the past. They swiftly defeat the Legionnaires, leaving only the powerless Karate Kid to face off against the Legion's two toughest members.
name: Unearthly Possessions

description:
Part 1 of the 4-part "Legion of the Damned!" It's just one short month, but the alien threat known only as the Blight (introduced in LEGION Secret Files #2) has completely taken over Earth and possessed its inhabitants. Only a few Legionnaires remain, but they may not last long, since the Blight are using the team's former colleagues to hunt them down and crush the last of Earth's resistance!

Continued in Legionnaires #79
name: Legion Of The Damned, Part One

description:
The secrets of the Blight are revealed in Part 3 of the 4-part "Legion of the Damned!" But will that information help XS, the super- speeding Legionnaire who's in for the run of her life against her own mind-controlled teammates inside the Blight headquarters known as the Stem? Also, is there a traitor in the Legion's midst?

Continued in Legionnaires #80
name: Legion of the Damned, Part Three: Damned If We Don't!

description:
The battle with the Blight may be over, but the repercussions are greater than ever. A war-ravaged Earth has been quarantined by the United Planets, the blame for the Blight invasion has been placed on U.P. President Brande, and the Legion's existence is also called into question! Continued in LEGIONNAIRES #81.

The Legion handle life after the threat of the Blight.
name: Widening Rifts Part 1: Childhood's End

description:
The series' final issue, "Widening Rifts" part 3, continued from LEGIONNAIRES #81. Against the United Planets' protests, the Legion makes one final effort to save the galaxy from the lethal rift that grows within the corrupted Stargate network. Unfortunately, even if the solution saves the galaxy, it will most likely destroy the entire Legion!

This is the last issue of this volume. The story of the Legion of Super-Heroes continues in Legion Lost.

A rift tears the very fabric of time and space and threaten the universe. Several members of the Legion of Super-Heroes risk their lives in fixing the rift and they get sucked through.
name: Widening Rifts Conclusion: Extinction Event

description: He's the man who broke Batman's back, a hideous creature who laughs at danger and defies death. But take a moment to crawl inside Bane's head and you'll find...unrequited love?!? When Bane forms an unlikely alliance with Black Canary, she may just find herself a man on the rebound! Ewwwwww. And how is it "This Issue: Batman Dies?!?
name: The Suitor

description:
"Officer Down," Part 3. While her father clings to life, Oracle gathers Batman's allies: Nightwing, Robin, Azrael, and Batgirl. Their mission: capture Catwoman before the police find her. But the search for Catwoman leads them into an unexpected trap.

Spoilers

Batman instructs the other heroes of Gotham to find Catwoman - even if she didn't shoot Gordon, she probably knows who did. Batman himself tells Oracle that he will stay with James Gordon, despite all her protests that he should be helping find the gunman. He is unmoved, and Oracle sends the others out on a mission to some of Catwoman's former associates, who are 'persuaded' to give them the location of Catwoman's probable target for the night.

Alfred visits Gordon's bedside to see if he can be of any help or comfort to Batman, but is completely ignored. Meanwhile, Chief Akins announces his temporary promotion to the rest of the department, the heroes watch Catwoman attempt entry to the Burnett museum, and Officers Rich and Lowell try to find some witnesses to the shooting...to absolutely no avail.

At the museum, the heroes defeat the robber's henchmen, and move in on the woman, only to discover that it is not Catwoman at all, but a disguised Harley Quinn. She tells them that Catwoman is not responsible for the shooting but is in hiding, in fear of her life. She decides to tell them where Catwoman is on condition that they won't hurt her feline pal.

Officer Down continues in Catwoman #90
name: Officer Down -- Part Three: Armed and Dangerous

description: Part 1 of the 3-Part "History Lesson!" So whatever happened to the mercenary group the Ravens, who were lost way back in the past in issue #5? The mystery begins when a trio of Vikings burst forth from a S.T.A.R. Laboratory, and deepens when an ancient relic is uncovered with an inexplicable connection to Black Canary. Oracle sends Canary on the trail, but the doorway to the past goes in both directions. As Canary begins her perilous journey, will she find herself ending up in the history books?
name: History Lesson -- Part One: Time to Kill

description: Part 2 of the 3-part "History Lesson!" Black Canary is lost in the past looking for the murderous Ravens, but her one possible ally, a Viking, has hidden motives. And Canary's knowledge of how history will play out, especially who lives and who dies, just may get her killed!
name: History Lesson, Part 2: Valhalla, Baby!

description: Part 3 of the 3-part "History Lesson!" It's Viking action just the way your parents described it! As the raging hordes close in on Canary and her unlikely allies, the Ravens, Oracle tries desperately to pierce the misty veil of time to contact her missing colleague. But if she succeeds, then not only will Canary be saved, but Cheshire will return to the present as well, where she'll murder several helpless S.T.A.R. Labs employees! Either way, Canary can't win!
name: History Lesson -- Part Three: Time and Time and Time Again!

description: It's star-crossed love and the gentle art of...stalking your friends?!? Jason Bard, detective extraordinaire, is called in to track the movements of Black Canary. But who called him onto the case, and why? And speaking of Canary, who's that tall, dark stranger she seems to have formed a special friendship with? We'll give you a hint: He's old. He's really, really old. Featuring gorgeous guest-pencils by newcomer Michael McDonnell.
name: The Big Romance

description: Bean Bandit is going to spring Gray from jail, and Rally Vincent knows it. Given that Gray is gunning for Rally, that knowledge should give her time to plan for their face-to-face. But the best laid plans of mice and Gunsmiths. . .

Gray has Minnie, Bean has Gray, and now . . . the police have Rally Vincent! Before she can rescue her friend, Rally is arrested by furious Minnesota police. Can she get out of the can before her best friend winds up in a coffin? Only time -- and the third issue of Shades of Gray -- will tell!
name: SIG-SG550

description: Not a bullet to the chest or a knife in the stomach. Instead, it looks like it'll be a freight container on the head that ends Rally Vincent's bounty-hunting career! Rally and Minnie-May, the Gunsmith Cats, are cornered by Gray in an airfreight warehouse, and it's going to be terminal if they can't find their way out!
name: Lost
